      {
        "id": "834885f15914fc6a03a8a6612269386c5b520fd1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3949,
          "name": "Lasse Kaihlavirta",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "l.kaihlavirt@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "kaihlavi"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-11-04 18:10:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe purpose of this initial commit is to see that \n- gerrit commit triggers the execution of all the jobs in sequence\n- the result of the jobs comes back to the review as verification vote correctly\n\nThe implementation came out even more hacky than I hoped, and there are quite a number of things that should be addressed:\n- the naming of the triggered jobs in the template is taken from what music already provides now and needs to be improved in final version\n- selection of CSIT job is now hacked around with additional \"review-functionality\" parameter - the final implementation should be able to trigger all the jobs generated from different functionalities without separate parameter\n- I'm not sure if the unified review job should be defined in integration csit templates at all (nor taken in use in project's csit - but I couldn't make it immediately work any other way)\n- I'm somewhat confused by the different variations of project name and their proper use",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "1e38daf04388bd3baa9f2fa2cadab23a75288222",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3949,
          "name": "Lasse Kaihlavirta",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "l.kaihlavirt@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "kaihlavi"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-11-04 18:14:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAlso,\n\n- the triggered docker build and CSIT jobs are still original jobs and do not take or use the UNIQUE_DOCKER_TAG for anything",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
